What is the structure of your dataset?</br> There are 113 937 loans in the dataset with 81 characteristics for each loan, such as the amount of the loan, the interest rate, its current status, the borrower's income, and many others. Apparently there is some missing data in our dataset foe feature like CreditGrade , ClosedDate and too many other featues

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?</br> ProsperScore : To score the risk ProsperRating (Alpha)

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?</br>

  • ListingCategory : The category of the listing that the borrower selected when posting their listing.</br>
  • BorrowerState: The state of the address of the borrower at the time the Listing was created.</br>
  • Occupation: The Occupation selected by the Borrower at the time they created the listing.</br>
  • EmploymentStatus: The employment status of the borrower at the time they posted the listing</br>
  • EmploymentStatusDuration: The length in months of the employment status at the time the listing was created.</br>
  • IsBorrowerHomeowner: A Borrower will be classified as a homowner if they have a mortgage on their credit profile or provide documentation confirming they are a homeowner.</br>
  • LoanOriginalAmount: The origination amount of the loan.</br>
  • StatedMonthlyIncome: The income range of the borrower at the time the listing was created.</br>
  • Term: The length of the loan expressed in months</br>
  • BorrowerRate : The Borrower's interest rate for this loan. </br>

Univariate Exploration </br> I'll start by looking at the distribution of the main variable of interest:</br>

ProsperScore</br> BorrowerAPR</br>

I need to subset the dataframe by selecting features of interest and the features that help support my investigation

#define a function we will use when ploting simple vertical Barcharts
def BarChart_vertical(data, feature , title):
    ax= sb.countplot(data=data, x=feature);
    ax.set_title(title)
In [13]:
#define a function we will use when ploting simple horizontal  Barcharts
def BarChart_horizantal(data, feature , title):
    sb.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(12,9)})
    sb.countplot(data = data, y =feature) 
    plt.xlabel(title);
